    <text>
        <body>
            <head>F29 [Gaede]</head>

            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_37" xml:lang="grc" n="1">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.43@πολυπίδακον-13.1.43@αὐτῶν">Strab. 13, 1, 43:</ref> 
                        πολυπίδακον δὲ τὴν <geogName type="mountain" key="Ida" nymRef="Ἴδη" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550592">Ἴδην</geogName> 
                        ἰδίως οἴονται λέγεσθαι διὰ τὸ πλῆθος τῶν ἐξ αὐτῆς ῥεόντων ποταμῶν καθ’ἃ μάλιστα ἡ 
                        <placeName type="region" key="dardania" nymRef="Δαρδανική">Δαρδανικὴ</placeName> ὑποπέπτωκεν αὐτῇ (καὶ) μέχρι 
                        <placeName type="city" key="skepsis" nymRef="Σκῆψις" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550890">Σκήψιος</placeName> καὶ τὰ
                        περὶ <placeName type="city" key="ilion" nymRef="Ἴλιον" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550595">Ἴλιον</placeName>. 
                        ἔμπειρος δ’ὢν τῶν τόπων ὡς ἂν ἐπιχώριος ἀνὴρ ὁ <persName key="demetriosskepsis" nymRef="Δημήτριος ὁ Σκήψιος"><name>Δημήτριος</name></persName> 
                        τοτὲ μὲν οὕτως λέγει περὶ αὐτῶν 
                    </seg>
                        
                        <seg type="fragment" resp="demetrios" xml:id="troic-diac" n="2">
                            <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001.radt:13.1.43@ἔστι-13.1.43@Αἴσηπος"/>
                            <cit>
                                <quote>ἔστι γὰρ λόφος τις τῆς <geogName type="mountain" key="Ida" nymRef="Ἴδη" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550592">Ἴδης</geogName>
                                    <geogName type="mountain" key="cotylos" nymRef="Κότυλος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550668">Κότυλος</geogName>· 
                                    ὑπέρκειται δ’οὗτος ἑκατόν που καὶ εἴκοσι σταδίοις <placeName type="city" key="skepsis" nymRef="Σκῆψις" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550890">Σκήψιος</placeName> 
                                    ἐξ οὗ ὅ τε <geogName type="river" key="scamandrus" nymRef="Σκάμανδρος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/465994">Σκάμανδρος</geogName> 
                                    ῥεῖ καὶ ὁ <geogName type="river" key="granicus" nymRef="Γράνικος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511260">Γράνικος</geogName> καὶ 
                                    <geogName type="river" key="aesepus" nymRef="Αἴσηπος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511141">Αἴσηπος</geogName></quote>
                            </cit>
                        </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="3">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.43@οἱ-13.1.45@ἀπελίπομεν">until § 45 C603 inspired by Demetrios</ref>
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>


            <div type="apparatus"/>

            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" n="1">
                <ab>
                <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="1"><title>Strab. 13, 1, 43:</title> 
                    It is believed that <geogName type="mountain" key="Ida" nymRef="Ἴδη"
                        ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550592">Mount Ida</geogName> is
                    pointedly called "many-fountained" because of the great number of rivers taking
                    their spring from there, in particular in the region where the <placeName
                        type="region" key="dardania" nymRef="Δαρδανική">Dardanian plain</placeName> lies beneath it
                         until <placeName type="city" key="skepsis" nymRef="Σκῆψις"
                        ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550890">Scepsis</placeName> and the
                    territory of <placeName type="city" key="ilion" nymRef="Ἴλιον"
                        ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550595">Ilion</placeName>. <persName key="demetriosskepsis" nymRef="Δημήτριος ὁ Σκήψιος"
                            ><name>Demetrios</name></persName>, being, as a native, well-acquainted
                    with these places, spoke once in this way about them:</seg> 
                    
                    <seg type="fragment" resp="demetrios" n="2">
                        <quote>there is indeed a hill of <geogName type="mountain" key="Ida" nymRef="Ἴδη"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550592">Mount Ida</geogName>,
                        called <geogName type="mountain" key="cotylos" nymRef="Κότυλος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550668">Kotylos</geogName>; it lies
                        about a hundred and twenty stadia above <placeName type="city" key="skepsis"
                            nymRef="Σκῆψις" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550890"
                            >Scepsis</placeName> and from it flow the <geogName type="river"
                            key="scamandrus" nymRef="Σκάμανδρος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/465994">Scamander</geogName>, the
                            <geogName type="river" key="granicus" nymRef="Γράνικος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511260">Granicos</geogName> and the
                            <geogName type="river" key="aesepus" nymRef="Αἴσηπος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511141"
                    >Aesepus</geogName>,</quote>
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>


            <div type="commentary">
                <p/>
            </div>

